cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the properties of positive-definite kernels that mimic computation in large neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of these kernels for classification tasks, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses tools from differential geometry to analyze the geometry of surfaces in Hilbert space, which is a topic in both neural networks (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SI).
